Johannesburg - President Jacob Zuma has re-appointed
Competition Tribunal chairperson Norman Manoim and four other members for
another five years, the presidency said on Monday. Mondo Mazwai was appointed as a new full-time member of
the tribunal, Mac Maharaj said in a statement. The appointments took effect on 1 August and would end on
31 July 2019. The re-appointed members of the tribunal are Andreas
Wessels and Yasmin Carrim as full-time members, and Andiswa Ndoni and Medi
Mokuena as part-time members. "We wish all the members of the Competition Tribunal
all the best in this critical endeavour," Zuma said.